This Makefile builds all c and c++ files into independant executable files.
The source files are taken from the directory defined by variable 'srcdir', and built in irectory defined by variable 'buildir'.

This would represent the structure:
==========
<current directory>
        |
        |-<srcdir>
        |    |-<cfiles>
        |    |-<c++ files>
        |
        |-<buildir>
        |    |-<c object files>
        |    |-<cxx object files>
        |    |-<executables>
        |
        |-<Makefile>
        |-<helper scripts>

the following variables give more control over the build proccess
#====Compiler flags====#
CC		(defualt 'gcc')
CLIBS		(defualt no value)
CFLAGS		(defualt '-g -O -Wall')
CXX		(defualt 'g++')
CXXLIBS		(defualt no value)
CXXFLAGS	(defualt '-g -O -Wall')
#====Install configuration====#
prefix		(/usr/local)
DESTDIR		(defualt no value)
#====Program Names====#
prog_name	(defualt 'mainc')
cxxprog_name	(defualt 'maincxx')
#=====================#

The variables:
srcdir		(value './src')
buildir		(value './build')
Are not meant to be set from commandline!
